## Datasource References — Always Use Full UUID Path, Never Short Aliases

**Rule:** Datasources are keyed by UUID. Always use the full `collections.UUID.data.*` path in every fragment, screen, action, and condition. **Never** create `store.json` computed aliases (e.g. `product.name → collections.UUID.data.product.name`) as a shortcut — always write the full path directly.

**Why:** Computed aliases add indirection, hide where data comes from, and create subtle merge-order bugs with the variable store. Full paths are explicit and always correct.

**UUID map for this project:**

| Short name | UUID | Root data path |
|---|---|---|
| Product detail | `b2c3d4e5-f6a7-8901-bcde-f12345678901` | `collections.UUID.data.product.*` |
| Cart | `a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890` | `collections.UUID.data.activeOrder.*` |
| Checkout active order | `b8c9d0e1-f2a3-4567-bcde-678901234567` | `collections.UUID.data.activeOrder.*` |
| Collection (search) | `d4e5f6a7-b8c9-0123-defa-234567890123` | `collections.UUID.data.search.*` |
| Search | `e5f6a7b8-c9d0-1234-efab-345678901234` | `collections.UUID.data.search.*` |
| Featured products | `c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-123456789012` | `collections.UUID.data.search.items` |
| Nav collections | `a7b8c9d0-e1f2-3456-abcd-567890123456` | `collections.UUID.data.collections.items` |

**Examples:**
```json
// ❌ BAD — short path alias
"text": "{{product.name}}"
"map": "collection.search.items"
"condition": "collections['b8c9d0e1-f2a3-4567-bcde-678901234567']?.data?.activeOrder?.shippingLines?.length > 0"

// ✅ GOOD — full UUID path
"text": "{{collections.b2c3d4e5-f6a7-8901-bcde-f12345678901.data.product.name}}"  (text template)
"map": "collections.d4e5f6a7-b8c9-0123-defa-234567890123.data.search.items"
"condition": "collections['b8c9d0e1-f2a3-4567-bcde-678901234567']?.data?.activeOrder?.shippingLines?.length > 0"
```

**Key distinction:**
- **Text templates** (`"text"`, `"map"`, `"key"` fields) use `{{collections.UUID.data.path}}` dot-notation (resolved by the template engine)
- **Formula expressions** (`"condition"`, `{ "formula": "..." }`) use `collections['UUID']?.data?.path` bracket + optional-chaining notation (evaluated as plain JavaScript)

**UI state paths** (written by `setVar`/`increment`/`toggle` to the variable store) are NOT datasource data — these correctly use short paths:
- `product.imageIndex`, `product.selectedOptions` — UI state for product page interactions
- `collectionSkip`, `searchSkip` — pagination offsets
- `nav.searchQuery`, `nav.themeMenuOpen`, `nav.colorScheme` — UI state

**Auto-fetch:** `extractReferencedDataSources` scans bindings for `collections.UUID` patterns and auto-fetches matching datasources. Using full UUID paths is what triggers this auto-fetch mechanism — short aliases would silently disable it.

