## searchParamSync — Config-Driven, No Hardcoding in Page

**Rule:** `app/[[...slug]]/page.tsx` must not hardcode paths. All sync behavior comes from `config/variables.json` `urlParam` entries. Query params are accessed directly via `globalContext.browser.query.*` in formulas and datasource variables.

**Optional fields per `urlParam` def (in `config/variables.json`):**

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| `param` | string | URL query parameter name (e.g. `q`, `sort`, `page`) |
| `default` | string | Default value when param is absent from URL |
| `triggersParamChange` | boolean | When true, URL change triggers `paramChangeAction` for the route |
| `routePrefix` | string | When set, only apply this sync when pathname.startsWith(routePrefix) |
| `transform` | string | e.g. `"pageToSkip"` converts page number to skip offset |

**Reading query params in formulas/datasources:** Use `globalContext.browser.query.*` directly — no `route.*` paths needed:
```json
"term": { "formula": "globalContext?.browser?.query?.q" },
"sort": { "formula": "globalContext?.browser?.query?.sort || 'name-asc'" },
"cacheKeyVars": ["globalContext.browser.query.q", "globalContext.browser.query.sort"]
```

**Never hardcode in page.tsx** — use `urlParam` entries in `variables.json` and `triggersParamChange` in config instead.

